<Content> The restaurant definately looks elegant and is impressive. It is clear why it was voted best date place in champaign. The menu is interesting, expensive, and not kid friendly, though that appears intentional, since they want big checks, not big families.Veggie option on the menue I had was tofu veggie stirbfry, but when it came, it had zero tofu. strange given the dish was called tofu vegetable stirfry. The waiter never checked in on us after our food arrived until we were finished. He showed me an updated menu in which there was no tofu in the stir fry, too bad I had an old menu - he didn't appologize, just said that he will make sure to remove the old menus from the stack. thanks... My daughter liked the dumplings and california roll. the edamame are served with sesame oil, which is a nice touch. The waiter refilled my daughter's lemonade with ice water - thanks for that, too.... My son objected when he tried to fill his sprite with water . My son and wife liked the steak. Dessert was good according to my kids though they didn't finish it, so it couldn't have been that good. I've not seen them fail to finish chocolate cake before. In all, it's over priced, decent food with not so great service, but excellent ambiance. Great for impressing your date, but not necessarily great food or service.
<Date> 2011-11-12
<Overall> 2.0

